    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Infinite-Powers-Calculus-Reveals-Universe/dp/1328879984" target="_self">“Infinite Powers” by Steven Strogatz</a> is one of those titles that you may have seen already as you scroll Amazon or Audible. If you have a Kindle, “Infinite Powers” is free on Kindle Unlimited, and there is also an audiobook to go along with it on Audible. The same can’t be said about the other two books in this list.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">“Infinite Powers” is a great pair with “Calculus Made Easy,” because it explores the wonders of calculus and reveals its roots in human history. You can think of “Calculus Made Easy” as the assignment, and “Infinite Powers” as the awe-inspiring lecture.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Strogatz goes into more detail than Bellos, because this text is specific to calculus. When did calculus first become prevalent? What shaped modern calculus? What around us uses calculus? All of these are questions that will be answered in this book, and Strogatz continually stresses the beauty of this subject.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
